Instead of ...d6-d5 Black should go for ` 2rqr1k1/1b2bppp/p2pp3/1p4Pn/3NP3/PPN1BP2/1P2Q2P/1K1R2R1 b - - 2 17 '  17...Qc7⁉ instead. However, I still think that after 18.h4 the position seems to be quite good for White, since Black has time to ...d6-d5 perfectly, and would most likely have to give up the pawn in order to get counterplay. If Black does not do this, then ideas like f4-f5 can become extremely dangerous in the future. } ) *

