10. h4 $5  {[%cal Gg4g5][%csl Gg5]} ( { A natural follow-up. Going } 10.g5 { straight is also fine, but I felt it is unnecessary to analyse lines with } 10...Bxg5 { . } ) Nc5 ( 10...Bxh4? { Falls to } 11.g5! Bxg5 12.Qh5 h6 13.f4 Be7 14.O-O-O $18 { and now White is simply winning because of the open g & h files. The next move should be Rdg1 and you (or rather, your opponent) should get ready to sacrifice something :) } ) 
11. g5 b5 
12. Rg1 $5  {[%cal Rh4h5,Rg5g6][%csl Gg5]} { Overprotecting the g5-pawn and threatening h5-g6 next. } b4 $5  {[%csl Rc3,Re4]} { Fighting fire with fire. } 
13. Nd5 {[%mdl 32768]} { The point. At this point in the course, such moves should be a regular occurence :) } exd5? { Biting the bait. In my experience, I've observed that opponents seldom accept sacrifices readily. However, mastering the art of executing sacrifices not only enhances your confidence but also fosters a mindset that embraces risk-taking, thereby priming you to employ strategic/dynamic sacrifices in the future, which is a skill necessary to play the Sozin successfully. } 
14. Bxd5 {[%cal Rd5g8,Gd5a8][%csl Ra8,Gd5,Rf7]} Bb7 
15. Nf5! {[%cal Gd1d4][%csl Gd4,Rg7]} { Logical follow-up. The immediate threat is Qd4. } Bxd5 ( 15...Nbd7? { Cracking under pressure. } 16.Bxc5 Bxd5 ( 16...Nxc5 17.Qd4 $18 { With a mate to follow. } ) 17.Qd4! { An important intermezzo. } 17...Ne5 18.O-O-O { And now both pieces in the center are pinned! } { Bxa2 19.Nxe7+ Qxe7 20.Bxd6+- And we win the piece back with interest. } ) 
16. Qxd5 {[%cal Gd5a8][%csl Ra8]} Nbd7 
17. h5 { Continuing the pawn storm and threatening g5-g6 next. Black has to be very, very careful to not end up in a dead lost position. The following line is not mandatory to learn, I have only added the best line according to the engine just to show what happens at the end. } ( 17.h5 17...Rc8 18.g6 Nf6 19.Nh6+! Kh8 20.Nxf7+ Rxf7 21.Qxf7 $40 { We already have sufficient material, while the kingside attack is still very much alive. } { 19...gxh6 $4 Leads to a pretty finish. 20.gxf7+ Kh8 21.Bxh6 $18 With Bg7 to follow. } ) *

