[Event "Fischer's Weapon Against the Najdorf: The Sozin Attack"]
[White "Thematic Exercises"]
[Black "Vidit, Santosh Gujrathi vs. Robson, Ray, Chess.com 2024"]
[Date "2024.12.18"]
[Result "1-0"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "rn2k2r/2qbbppp/p2ppn2/1p6/3NP3/PBN1B3/1PP1QPPP/2KR3R b kq - 0 11"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/48229077"]

11... Nc6 {[%mdl 32768]} 
12. g4 { This position occured in an online knockout rapid tournament. If I remember correctly, Vidit was down in the match (1.5-0.5 to Robson) and he was in a must win situation in order to qualify to the next round. Vidit won the game in a pretty convincing fashion - however, he had a better move in this position. White to play. } { In principle, I think this move is quite easy to find. There is no need to play f3 since the queen on e2 already protects the g4-square. The follow-up, is a bit more challenging. } ( { The game continued with: } 12.f4 Na5 13.Kb1 Nxb3 14.cxb3 Qb7 15.Bc1 { Soon Vidit found advantage with e5 and went on to win the game. } ) Nxd4 { If Black does not take, then g5 would be extremely dangerous. } 
13. Bxd4 e5 {[%csl Rd4,Rg4]} 
14. Be3 Bxg4 
{ This is a critical moment. White to play! } 15. Nd5! {[%csl Rc7,Rf6,Rg4]} { A pretty cute trick. It's one of those moments when all exchanges/simplification seems to work in your favour. } ( 15.f3 { I think this move deserves a mention. We have just sacrified a pawn but also opened the g-file which keeps the black king in the center, at least for now. } 15...Be6 16.Rhg1! { Provoking ...g6. } 16...g6 ( 16...O-O $6 { Leads to a pretty continuation. } 17.Bh6 Ne8 18.Rxg7+! Nxg7 19.Qg2 Bf6 20.Rg1 $18 ) 17.Bh6 { Stopping castling completely. I think we have achieved more than we bargained for - Black will eventually castle on the kingside and in that time you should launch the kingside attack via h4-f4-h5 etc. } ) Bxe2 ( 15...Nxd5 { Leads to disaster. } 16.Qxg4 Nxe3 17.Qxg7! O-O-O 18.fxe3 $18 { White is winning due to complete domination over the light-squares. } ) 
16. Nxc7+ Kd7 
17. Nxa8 Rxa8 
18. Rde1 $16  { The position is not winning, but it's nice to be up an exchange :-) } 1-0

